<statement><p>If Pipe A can fill a tank in <m>{5}</m> hours, and Pipe B can fill the same tank in <m>{10}</m> hours:</p>

<p>a) What fraction of the tank does Pipe A fill in 1 hour?<br/>
<fillin characters="6" name="ans1"/>  </p>

<p>b) What fraction of the tank does Pipe B fill in 1 hour?<br/>
<fillin characters="6" name="ans2"/>   </p>

<p>c) If both pipes work together, what fraction of the tank do they fill in 1 hour?<br/>
<fillin characters="6" name="ans3"/>    </p>

<p>d) How long will it take to fill the tank if both pipes work together?<br/>
<fillin characters="6" name="ans4"/>  hours </p></statement><solution><p>Worked Solution</p>
<p><strong>Part (a):</strong><br/>
Pipe A fills tank in <m>{5}</m> hours<br/>
In 1 hour: fills <m> \frac{1}{5} </m> of tank (reciprocal of time)</p>

<p><strong>Part (b):</strong><br/>
Pipe B fills tank in <m>{10}</m> hours<br/>
In 1 hour: fills <m> \frac{1}{10} </m> of tank (reciprocal of time)</p>

<p><strong>Part (c):</strong><br/>
Fraction of tank filled by the 2 tanks in 1 hour: <m> \frac{1}{5} + \frac{1}{10} = {\frac{3}{10}}</m> of tank</p>

<p><strong>Part (d):</strong><br/>
Time to fill tank together = Reciprocal of combined rate<br/>
Time = <m> \frac{1}{{\frac{3}{10}}} ={\frac{10}{3}}</m> hours</p></solution><answer><p><m>\frac{1}{5}</m></p></answer>
<answer><p><m>\frac{1}{10}</m></p></answer>
<answer><p><m>\frac{3}{10}</m></p></answer>
<answer><p><m>\frac{10}{3}</m></p></answer>
